{
  "stem": "17426.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But my brother had a very, very pompous bar mitzvah, in which he was then a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was supposed to go to yeshiva, and he was supposed to be a very Orthodox, religious, pious student after yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He changed his mind obviously, afterwards.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I remember the rabbi was forecasting that he is going to be one of the town's great yeshiva [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, but my bar mitzvah, when I was bar mitzvahed, it was already during the times that Hitler has already spread, spilt his venom over the border to Poland.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Poland already emulated Hitler's pogroms and Hitler's [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [? braving ?] of Jews and so forth.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my bar mitzvah was just very small in temple, where I was given an aliyah in my bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, there were four synagogues in a small town like Dobra for 150 families.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was only about 300, 400, 400 souls, and there were four synagogues.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was rivalry beyond, beyond explanation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On some holidays, there was blood running on the, on the-- between one shtiebel and the other shtiebel in the temple.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My father was a member of the large temple, which was the [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] temple that most Jews were-- I would say medium well-to-do Jews.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The rest of them were divided into three different groups.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One was the [INAUDIBLE] shtiebel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was a shtiebel rather than a shul.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was a small room, in which a number, like 40 or 50, would meet in the vicinity of the temple.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was all in one particular yard.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the next one was the Alexander [INAUDIBLE], which was also separate.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was more progressive, not quite as orthodox as the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
